image.altText: A man wearing black rimmed glasses, black suit and yellow tie stands in front of a group of media microphones speaking.

props.synopsis: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese says "there is no place for this hateful ideology here in Australia" following the arrest of 16 National Socialist Network members on Sunday.

title.children: PM condemns 'horrific scenes' of neo-Nazi gathering in Adelaide

image.altText: aerial shot of Adelaide's water desalination plant

props.synopsis: Desalination production south of Adelaide is set to quadruple as local reservoirs fall to 44 per cent capacity, with dry conditions causing the lowest inflows in over 40 years.

title.children: Desalination plant to 'ramp up' as reservoir levels drop to 20-year low

image.altText: A beached beaked whale near a river

props.synopsis: A wildlife ranger says the discovery of a beached whale, believed to be a beaked whale, on South Australia's Kangaroo Island is a "peculiar" occurrence.

title.children: 'Elusive deep-water' whale found beached on Kangaroo Island

image.altText: An SA Police vehicle with flashing lights.

props.synopsis: A 20-year-old woman is airlifted to hospital after she was struck by a boat allegedly being operated by a woman with a blood alcohol concentration nearly three times the legal limit.

title.children: Swimmer airlifted to hospital after being struck by boat on River Murray

image.altText: Three police officers standing in the Adelaide parklands

props.synopsis: Sixteen neo-Nazis have been arrested, and one charged with displaying a Nazi symbol, following a march in Adelaide's CBD.

title.children: SA Police arrest 16 neo-Nazis after march in Adelaide's CBD

image.altText: A variety of rubbish, including a swing set, dumped on a brown forest floor, with green trees behind

props.synopsis: Forestry companies say a rise in rubbish dumping increases fire hazards in an already high-risk summer, and it is costing them thousands of dollars to clean up.

title.children: Lack of education blamed for rubbish being dumped in forests

image.altText: Police officers standing on a street with police tape

props.synopsis: A woman has been rushed to hospital in a critical condition, and a man charged with attempted murder, after an alleged domestic assault in Adelaide's north-west.

title.children: Stabbing victim in critical condition after suspected domestic assault in Adelaide's north-west

props.synopsis: A shortage of qualified instructors has made adult swimming lessons harder to find despite a rise in drownings.

image.altText: woman looking out window

props.synopsis: There’s a push for stricter regulation of the massage industry, after a practitioner was able to keep indecently assaulting his clients after being reported to police and an industry body. Data shows the issue could be widespread.

title.children: The massage industry is self-regulated. These women want that to change

image.altText: A woman in a wheelchair at the beach

props.synopsis: An Adelaide woman has called for the expansion of South Australia's beach access program to encourage more people with disabilities to enjoy the ocean.

title.children: Calls to expand SA beach access so ocean can be enjoyed by all

image.altText: A semi-trailer trailer on fire at night

props.synopsis: A semitrailer carrying toilet paper catches fire while driving through dry farmland and pine forests in south-western Victoria, but "luck" and cooperation prevent the blaze from causing a much larger disaster.

image.altText: An elephant inside a cage with a zookeeper standing outside

image.altText: Penny Wong holds a press conference in a corridor in Parliament House

props.synopsis: Australia's foreign minister has delivered a message from Auschwitz urging unity "across political difference", where a delegation is marking the 80th anniversary of the concentration camp's liberation.

title.children: Speaking from Auschwitz, Wong urges unity 'across political difference'

props.synopsis: The world's most-awkward acronym, NAIRU, can predict where interest rates are heading and the signs are not good for borrowers.

title.children: Rate cut in February? Forget it

image.altText: Two officers take a man out of a paddy wagon at the day steet station after he was arrested over defacing police memoria wall

props.synopsis: The NSW Police Commissioner has praised the swift action of investigators after a man was arrested following the discovery of offensive markings at a memorial "sacrilege to officers".

title.children: Man arrested after 'despicable' vandalism of Sydney police memorial

image.altText: Joey Pamment stands in the sun in front of a construction site

props.synopsis: Australian small to medium enterprises expect the cost of doing business to rise this year but are keeping their sights on a reprieve from the Reserve Bank. A NAB survey found 22 per cent of businesses expect to see profitability decrease over the next year.

image.altText: a photo of a an older woman smiling at camera with glasses and grey hair

image.altText: A close up of the Colombian consulate sign with a flag in the background

props.synopsis: US President Donald Trump and Colombian President Gustavo Petro clash with fiery social media posts. But what about the people caught up in the diplomatic stoush?

title.children: What happens to the Colombians being deported from the US?

image.altText: Australia cricket player Travis Head, standing on the ground at training, wearing a batting helmet

props.synopsis: Travis Head says Australia will consider taking the radical step of changing the batting order mid-game against Sri Lanka.

props.synopsis: Around the clock coverage of news events as they break at home and abroad.

title.children: ABC News Channel live

image.altText: A small grey airplane at sunset

props.synopsis: A Brisbane-based aviation company is working with CQ University researchers to get Australia's first green hydrogen-powered commercial flight in the sky by 2027.

image.altText: A middle-aged bald man with glasses in a suit speaks outside.

props.synopsis: The cameo role US president Donald Trump may play in our imminent election campaign is the wildcard no-one can predict — and it is making political hardheads nervous.

image.altText: An aerial photo of Geelong showing the city and waterfront on a sunny blue sky day.

image.altText: A local council building

image.altText: A street view of a single-storey brick house next to a two-storey block of flats.

props.synopsis: More than two decades ago, the Tasmanian government sold a block of flats in a rural town. It turns out, it also "erroneously" transferred a house next door that a Sydney couple is claiming to own.

image.altText: Looking towards a crescent-shaped beach from the top of a small mountain.

image.altText: A stuffed kangaroo holding a sign that reads "RIP Angel".

title.children: Woman remanded in custody over alleged murder of 9yo Townsville boy

image.altText: Two small bento style lunchboxes filled with a variety of food.

image.altText: A Country Fire Authority four wheel drive parked on sandy grass near a dam with grey and white smoke billowing into the sky.

image.altText: weather map of queensland showing green and orange patches

image.altText: Alexander Zverev and Jannik Sinner pose with their trophies

image.altText: A dingo in bushland.

image.altText: A man ina suit with a  pink and blue tie speaking at a press conference.

props.synopsis: Jarrod Bleijie says he's seen a "newly revised" Infrastructure Priority List which shows the number of Queensland projects has been reduced from 29 to seven.

title.children: Queensland deputy premier says he 'won't cop' federal infrastructure cuts

image.altText: Air Vanuatu igat hevi (FB: Air Vanuatu)

props.synopsis: Plans to restart the collapsed national airline Air Vanuatu have raised concern among business and tourism leaders who say it shouldn't operate international flights again.

image.altText: A car with a crumpled front against a tree at night with the scene lit up and a yellow police evidence marker on the ground.

props.synopsis: Police allege the Kilmore East man was unlicensed when he veered off the road and crashed into a tree, leaving his female passenger with life threatening injuries.

title.children: Victorian driver charged after allegedly abandoning hurt passenger in crash
